Next, we will divide both equations with $\text{P}$:

$$\begin{aligned}
\frac{\cancel{\text{P}}}{\cancel{\text{P}}}+\frac{\cancel{\text{P}} \times \text{t} \times\text{r}_\text{s}}{\cancel{\text{P}}}&= \frac{\cancel{\text{P}} \times (1+\text{r}_\text{c})^{\text{t}}}{\cancel{\text{P}}}\\[15pt]
1+ \text{t} \times\text{r}_\text{s}&=(1+\text{r}_\text{c})^{\text{t}}
\end{aligned}$$

Finally, we will raise both equations to the power of $\dfrac{1}{\text{t}}$:

$$\begin{aligned}
(1+ \text{t} \times\text{r}_\text{s})^\frac{1}{\text{t}}&=1+\text{r}_\text{c}\\[10pt]
\text{r}_\text{c}&=\boxed{\left[(1+ \text{t} \times\text{r}_\text{s}\right)^\frac{1}{\text{t}}]-1}
\end{aligned}$$
